<p>In four different studies a regression analysis with one predictor is conducted. Consider the t-tests of the regression coefficient in the four different regression models below.
Which of the four different t-tests has the smallest p-value?</p>
<table class="table_shade">
<thead>
<tr class="header">
<th style="text-align: left;">Model</th>
<th style="text-align: left;">t_test</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td style="text-align: left;">I</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">t(29) = -1.3</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td style="text-align: left;">II</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">t(29) = 3.3</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td style="text-align: left;">III</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">t(299) = 1.3</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td style="text-align: left;">IV</td>
<td style="text-align: left;">t(299) = -3.3</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</p>]]></text>
