<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
<p>Model IV is correct. In general, larger t-values, regardless of whether itâ€™s a positive or negative value, are accompanied by smaller p-values. The sample size also has an influence. The same t-value (as in models II and IV) has a smaller associated p-value in a larger sample. So, according to this logic, the correct answer is model IV. The t-value and sample size (as shown by the df in the parentheses) are the largest here.</p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
